		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">EN 13402</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:282px;"><a href="/wiki/File:EN-13402-example-hiviz.jpg" class="image" title="Clothes-size label with EN&#160;13402-1 pictogram and body dimensions in centimetres (found on a high-visibility jacket sold in the United Kingdom)."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/EN-13402-example-hiviz.jpg/280px-EN-13402-example-hiviz.jpg" width="280" height="266" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:EN-13402-example-hiviz.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Clothes-size label with EN&#160;13402-1 <a href="/wiki/Pictogram" title="Pictogram">pictogram</a> and body dimensions in centimetres (found on a <a href="/wiki/High-visibility_clothing" title="High-visibility clothing">high-visibility</a> jacket sold in the United Kingdom).</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>EN 13402</b> is a European <a href="/wiki/Standardization" title="Standardization">standard</a> for labelling clothes sizes. It is based on body dimensions, measured in <a href="/wiki/Centimetre" title="Centimetre">centimetres</a>. It aims to replace many older national dress-size systems, most likely after the year <a href="/wiki/2007" title="2007">2007</a>. Acceptance of this form of standardization is likely to vary from country to country. For example, the Spanish Ministry of Health and Consumer Affairs has commissioned a study <a href="http://www.consumo-inc.es/Noticias/Notasdeprensa/2008/tallasIngles.htm" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.consumo-inc.es/Noticias/Notasdeprensa/2008/tallasIngles.htm" rel="nofollow">[1]</a> to categorise female body types with a view to harmonising Spanish clothing sizes with EN-13402. Few other countries are known to have followed suit.</p>
