<p>The secondary dimension <i>cup size</i> can be expressed in terms of the difference</p>
<dl>
<dd><i>cup size</i> = <i>bust girth</i> − <i>underbust girth</i></dd>
</dl>
<p>and can be labelled compactly using a letter code appended to the <i>underbust girth</i>:</p>
<table class="wikitable">
<tr align="center">
<th>Code</th>
<td>AA</td>
<td>A</td>
<td>B</td>
<td>C</td>
<td>D</td>
<td>E</td>
<td>F</td>
<td>G</td>
</tr>
<tr>
